image.altText: A Fijian rugby union player holds the ball as he attempts to evade a Wallabies opponent at the men's Rugby World Cup.

items.synopsis: Australia's Rugby World Cup campaign is dealt a major blow, with Fiji defeating the Wallabies 22-15 in a tense pool match in Saint-Étienne. Follow our live blog.

title.children: Fiji stuns Wallabies at Rugby World Cup to break 69-year drought

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Jubilation for the Fijians, who are still alive in the tournament! The players are on their haunches, and those that are not are hugging and celebrating. What a moment for Fiji. What a moment for Australia - whose tournament now hangs on getting a result against Wales next week.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: FIJI BEAT AUSTRALIA FOR THE FIRST TIME IN 69 YEARS!

children.content: Jubilation for the Fijians, who are still alive in the
The players are on their haunches, and those that are not are hugging and celebrating.
What a moment for Australia - whose tournament now hangs on getting a result against Wales next week.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Hope for the Wallabies! And it's Suli Vunivalu who provides it! The maul was established from the lineout and there was a penalty coming too as the Fijians are pinged for side entry to the rolling maul. That broke down but Vunivalu was on hand to dive over. Ben Donaldson is being booed and jeered but he nails the conversion. It's a one-try ball game! Australia trails 15-22.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 68' Wallabies score!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Jordan Uelese is laid out on his back after taking out Tevita Ikanivere off the ball. He tried to make a tackle but headbutted the substitute hooker in the hip. Fiji will kick for the posts through Frank Lomani, 33 metres out, dead in front. He makes it! Fiji's lead is out to 14! They lead 22-8!
